AWOL: ArchWiki Offline
Version: 0.1.2 (Alpha)
License: GPLv3
Copyright: (C) 2012  Tetractys Productions LLC.
Author: Exiquio Cooper-Anderson (exiquio [at] gmail [dot] com)

Description:

ArchWki Offline provides users an offline version of the popular Linux resource, ArchWiki. It is based on OpenZIM and relies on zimreader-java.
This software is alpha software and meant for testing purposes as development pushes forward towards a "feature complete" beta. 

Features:

-Offline access to the popular linux resource, ArchWiki (wiki.archlinux.org)
-Quickly load the most useful topics
-Quick search ArchWiki topics

Beta Roadmap:

-New Art and Color Scheme By Vivo aka ArtVictim
-Search Suggestions
-MenuActivity
-Search Menu Option
-Find In Page Menu Option (Implement Find in Page)
-Home Menu Option
-Settings Option (Implement Settings)
-ActionBar (mirror menu functionality)
-Removable Visual Zoom Controls 
-Bookmarks & Bookmark Menu Option
-Google Analytics Opt-In
-New ArchWiki ZIMFile
-Corrected Local URL loading
-Improved stability
-Unit/UI Testing

